                     <interp inst="def1-258-18391125" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-258-18391125" type="age" value="28"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-258-18391125" type="surname" value="GODWIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-258-18391125" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JAMES GODWIN</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18391125-258-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18391125-258-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18391125-258-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="stealingFromMaster"></interp> for stealing, on the <rs id="t18391125-cd-237" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18391125-258-offence-1 t18391125-cd-237"></join>25th of Oc<lb></lb>tober</rs>, 22 lbs. weight of lead, value 8<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. the goods of <persName id="t18391125-name-1276" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18391125-name-1276" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18391125-name-1276" type="surname" value="BRIGHTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18391125-name-1276" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18391125-258-offence-1 t18391125-name-1276"></join>John Brighton</persName>, his master.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18391125-name-1277" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18391125-name-1277" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18391125-name-1277" type="surname" value="BRIGHTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18391125-name-1277" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN BRIGHTON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a plumber, and live in Tooley-street—the pri<lb></lb>soner was in my employ for three months, as a labourer. On the 25th of October I left home at twelve o'clock, and went into the Borough—I re<lb></lb>turned in about twenty-five minutes, and met the prisoner going along a</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183911250176"></xptr>
               <p>street where he had no business, as I had left him in charge of the shop till I came home—I followed him into a marine-store shop—he went through the shop into the parlour, unbuttoned his clothes, pulled out a bit of lead, and put it on the hob—I then called out, "That is it, is it?"—he then turned and saw me—the man belonging to the shop was in the parlour with his wife—I said I would have a policeman—they begged I would not—I attempted to call out, but they shut the parlour-door, and shut me in—the prisoner said he would walk to the shop with me—I came out with him, and he attempted to escape, but I held him till the police-man came—I know the lead to be mine—he had no business with it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CLARKSON</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> How do you know it? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I saw it standing in the shop at twelve o'clock, and when I returned home I missed it from that place—I purchased it in the whole sheet—there is no mark on it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18391125-name-1278" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18391125-name-1278" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18391125-name-1278" type="surname" value="M'CORMACK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18391125-name-1278" type="given" value="PATRICK"></interp>PATRICK M'CORMACK</persName>
                  </hi>. I was sent for, and took the prisoner into cus<lb></lb>tody.</p>
